<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Valentine</persName>,
                                    assistant district attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">Field</persName>, Acting Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Philadelphia</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-08-16"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 16, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">W. A. Field</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting Attorney-General:</hi></p>
                            <p>The Hornet sailed Sunday morning, and was detained.</p>
                            <p>An examination will be made to-day, and the facts reported.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>JOHN K. VALENTINE,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Assistant United
                                        States Attorney.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>